Package: rnirs
Type: Package
Title: Locally Weighted PLS Regression and Discrimination
Version: 1.5-2
Author: Matthieu Lesnoff <matthieu.lesnoff@cirad.fr>
Maintainer: Matthieu Lesnoff <matthieu.lesnoff@cirad.fr>
Description: Package rnirs is a statistical tool box for locally weighted prediction 
  methods: regression (quantitative responses) and discrimination (qualitative responses). 
  The predictive models can use dimension reductions (such as PLS) or other methods
  The package was primarily dedicated to near infrared spectral data 
  but is generic for many other types of data.
Depends: R (>= 3.0.0)
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Imports:  data.table, FNN, ggplot2, gridExtra, ptw, scales, signal 
Suggests: knitr, rmarkdown
URL: https://github.com/mlesnoff/rnirs
License: GPL (>= 2)
LazyData: yes
